      "instructions": "Add potatoes to a large pot of boiling water. Cook until potatoes are fork tender. Drain. Add butter and mash potatoes until smooth. Add ¼ cup milk to potatoes and mix until potatoes are creamy. Add more milk as needed until you reach the desired texture. Season with salt and pepper to taste.While potatoes are cooking, heat a large skillet over medium-high heat, and cook ground beef until browned all the way through. Drain any excess grease.In a medium bowl, mix together cream of mushroom soup, Worcestershire sauce, and ketchup in a large bowl. Add soup mixture and corn to ground beef. Mix to combine. Cook over medium-low heat until everything is warmed through.Plate beef mixture and top with mashed potatoes. Top potatoes with some cheese, sour cream, and bacon.",
