      "instructions": "In a small {non-stick} skillet heat a teaspoon of bacon fat over medium heat.Add the sliced shallots and cook until soft. Add in the sliced mushrooms and cook for two minutes or until fragrant. Throw in the minced garlic and cook for one minute and remove the skillet off of the heat to cool.In a medium bowl whisk the three eggs and season with salt and pepper.Add in the mushroom/shallot mixture and the slice green onions, stir.Heat the same non-stick skillet over low heat and add in the remaining half teaspoon of bacon fat.Pour in the egg mixture and wait patiently as it sets. I adjusted heat between low and medium-low to help speed the whole process along.Once the egg mixture is almost set, sprinkle with the grated Jarlsberg.Carefully run a rubber spatula around the edges and underneath before folding in half. Sprinkle with a tablespoon of cheese.Cover with a lid to help melt the cheese before serving.Garnish with a sprinkle of sliced green onions or chopped chives.",
