      "instructions": "Procedures                                                                              1                                                                            In a blender, combine the onion, serranos, turmeric, garlic, ginger, cumin, and a couple tablespoons of water. Process until it is a smooth paste. Add a little more water if you need to.                                                                                                                             2                                                                            Pour the oil into a large skillet set over medium-high heat. Add the chicken pieces and the salt. Cook, stirring often, until the chicken browned, seven to ten minutes. Use a slotted spoon to remove the pieces and set aside, leaving as much of the fat behind.                                                                                                                             3                                                                            Reduce the heat to low and add the spice paste. Cook until very fragrant, about two minutes. Add the chicken back in, along with the tomato paste, and garam masala. Stir well, and cook until everything is combined, three to four minutes.                                                                                                                            4                                                                            Pour in the water and stir until mixture is combined. Cover the skillet, turn the heat to medium, and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.                                                                                                                             5                                                                            If needed, season to taste with salt. Serve the curry with a sprinkling of fresh cilantro and white rice.",
